article.headline: Austin Peay 70, Eastern Illinois 61
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Maurice Hampton went 3-for-5 from three-point range and hit all seven of his free throw attempts to finish with 22 points and lead Austin Peay over Eastern Illinois 70-61 Thursday night. Drake Reed added 12 points and Zac Schlader chipped in 10 for the Governors (14-11, 9-7 Ohio Valley), who outshot Eastern Illinois 50 percent to 38.5 percent for the game. Josh Gomes scored 19 points -- 12 off 3-pointers -- to lead the Panthers (5-17, 4-12). Mike Robinson scored 15 points, while George Tandy finished with 14 after hitting eight of eight free throw tries. Eastern Illinois managed 19 points off turnovers for the game and outscored the Governors in the second half despite 34.6 percent shooting, but weren't able to overcome a 10-point halftime deficit.
